<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="chromosome number">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Chromosome number.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">n</emphasis>
= 14 (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Onobrychis alba (Waldst. &amp; Kit.) Desv. subsp. echinata (Guss.) P. W. Ball, 2 n = 14. Scale bar: 10 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.8.49156.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/365693" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.8.49156.figure2">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="voucher specimen">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Voucher specimen.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
Italy. Puglia. Gravina di Leucaspide (Statte, Taranto) (WGS84: 
<geoCoordinate degrees="40.566319" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="40.56632">40.566319N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="17.190559" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="17.19056">17.190559E</geoCoordinate>
), gariga, 150 m s.l.m., 25 June 2019, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">L. Bernardo &amp; G. Maiorca</emphasis>
(CLU).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="method">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Method.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Squash preparations were made on root-tips obtained from germinating seeds. Root tips were pre-treated with 0.4% colchicine for 3 hours and then fixed in Carnoy fixative solution for 1 hour. After hydrolysis in HCl 1N at 60 °C, the tips were stained in leuco-basic fuchsine.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="observations">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Onobrychis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onobrychis alba" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="alba" subSpecies="echinata">Onobrychis alba subsp. echinata</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Southern Italy, where it occurs in Puglia, Basilicata, and Calabria. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263500012331350395" author="Cenci, CA" journalOrPublisher="Plant Biosystems" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="91 - 98" refId="B4" refString="Cenci, CA, Bassi, G, Ferranti, F, Romano, B, 2000. Some morphometric, anatomical and biochemical characteristics of fruits and seeds of Onobrychis spp. in Italy. Plant Biosystems 134: 91 - 98" title="Some morphometric, anatomical and biochemical characteristics of fruits and seeds of Onobrychis spp. in Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263500012331350395" volume="134" year="2000">Cenci et al. (2000)</bibRefCitation>
reported a chromosome number 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">n</emphasis>
= 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">x</emphasis>
= 14 for all the Italian subspecies of 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. alba" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">O. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but without providing any information about the source of these data. Therefore, we report here the first count safely attributable to a well-defined population of 
<taxonomicName genus="O." infraspecific-rank="subsp." lsidName="O. alba" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="subSpecies" species="alba" subSpecies="echinata">O. alba subsp. echinata</taxonomicName>
. This count is, however, in accordance with 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263500012331350395" author="Cenci, CA" journalOrPublisher="Plant Biosystems" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="91 - 98" refId="B4" refString="Cenci, CA, Bassi, G, Ferranti, F, Romano, B, 2000. Some morphometric, anatomical and biochemical characteristics of fruits and seeds of Onobrychis spp. in Italy. Plant Biosystems 134: 91 - 98" title="Some morphometric, anatomical and biochemical characteristics of fruits and seeds of Onobrychis spp. in Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263500012331350395" volume="134" year="2000">Cenci et al. (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pedrotti, F" journalOrPublisher="Informatore Botanico Italiano" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="47 - 51" refId="B10" refString="Pedrotti, F, Cortini Pedrotti, C, 1971. Numeri Cromosomici per la Flora Italiana: 13-18. Informatore Botanico Italiano 3: 47 - 51" title="Numeri Cromosomici per la Flora Italiana: 13 - 18." volume="3" year="1971">Pedrotti and Cortini Pedrotti (1971)</bibRefCitation>
reported the same chromosome number for a population of 
<taxonomicName genus="O." infraspecific-rank="subsp." lsidName="O. alba" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="subSpecies" species="alba" subSpecies="alba">O. alba subsp. alba</taxonomicName>
from Umbria. Our count supports the differentiation of this taxon from 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. calabrica" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="calabrica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">O. calabrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Širj">Sirj</normalizedToken>
., a tetraploid species with 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">n</emphasis>
= 4 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">x</emphasis>
= 28 chromosomes, endemic to a small area in south-eastern Calabria (
<bibRefCitation author="Bernardo, L" journalOrPublisher="Notiziario della Societa Botanica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="71 - 72" refId="B3" refString="Bernardo, L, Maiorca, G, Franzoni, J, Roma-Marzio, F, Peruzzi, L, 2018. Dati preliminari su Onobrychiscalabrica (Fabaceae) specie endemica italiana misconosciuta. Notiziario della Societa Botanica Italiana 2: 71 - 72" title="Dati preliminari su Onobrychiscalabrica (Fabaceae) specie endemica italiana misconosciuta." volume="2" year="2018">Bernardo et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
